---
// input: siteConfig data, gameData source, layout config
// output: Beginner guide page with detailed walkthrough steps and security guidelines
// pos: src/pages/guide.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
import { gameData } from "../data/game";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Beginner Guide | Roblox Loop and Defense" description="Read the official Merge a Nuke guide beginner guide to master the game loop. Merge bombs, collect offline cash, raid enemy bases, and lock your base safely.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Beginner guide</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Beginner Guide</h1>
      <p>{gameData.officialDescription}</p>
      <p class="source-label">Source: official Roblox listing, checked 2026-06-16.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.05); border: 1.5px solid rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 8px;">Beginner Tycoon Strategy</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Starting your nuclear empire in Roblox Merge a Nuke can feel overwhelming as you manage grid space and calculate multiplier benefits. Our comprehensive <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> is here to outline the essential progression loop. By mastering basic merging tactics, knowing when to run raids, and understanding the rebirth economy, you can accelerate your journey from a simple island outpost to a dominant military tycoon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Video Guide: How to Play and Merge Fast</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">Before diving into the detailed steps below, check out this video tutorial showing exactly how to merge nukes, manage your grid slots, and start generating serious cash fast.</p>
      <div style="margin: 24px 0; max-width: 800px; aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%;">
        <iframe 
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KG_lFaKZW1o" 
          title="Merge a Nuke Gameplay Walkthrough" 
          frameborder="0" 
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
          allowfullscreen
          style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-card); border: 1px solid var(--line);"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="starter-loop" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Core loop</p>
      <h2 id="starter-loop" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">What to do first</h2>
      
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">1</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Merge bombs upward</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">The core mechanic of Roblox Merge a Nuke involves spawning tier-1 missiles on your island and combining two identical missiles to unlock a higher tier. Each new tier increases your nuke collection stats and multiplier coefficients.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Managing your board is critical; if you spawn too many low-level bombs without combining them, your island grid will fill up, temporarily blocking new spawns. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> advises players to keep at least two grid slots open at all times to handle fast merging chains and avoid progression blockages.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Tip: Focus on clean merges to save grid space on your island before spending cash on spawning upgrades.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">2</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Watch your cash rate</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Nukes stored in your hangar generate passive cash over time. Higher tiers yield significantly more currency per minute. This offline income continues even while you are logged out of the Roblox server lobby.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">To optimize your economic efficiency, always calculate your cash rate before leaving the game. By reviewing your passive yield against the cost of your next hangar upgrade, you can estimate your progression curve. Our <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> provides a dedicated tool to help you model these upgrade gaps accurately.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Tip: Check the in-game display metrics to plan upgrade investments during away hours.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">3</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Raid with caution</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Launching high-tier nukes at other players' base islands steals a percentage of their cash and slows down their merging progress. However, this exposes you to retaliation from active servers.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Raiding is highly lucrative but risky. Before attacking a target, check their base layout and active multipliers. Engaging in endless raiding wars can distract you from merging, slowing your tycoon's core economy. Plan raids strategically when you need quick cash injections to hit upgrade milestones.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Tip: Avoid raiding players who have strong shield levels active or high rebirth multipliers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker">4</div>
          <div style="padding-left: 12px;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Lock your base</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">The game includes a base locking shield mechanic. Activating the lock protects your island from incoming raids and prevents other players from resetting your missile progress.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">An unlocked base is an easy target. If you leave the server with your shield deactivated, opponents can raid your hangar, setting back your cash accumulation. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends building a habit of activating the base lock shield before logging off to guarantee your offline progress is completely safe.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Tip: Always activate the lock shield before logging off to protect your accumulated offline earnings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="starter-safety" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Safety</p>
        <h2 id="starter-safety">Avoid risky shortcuts</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">No script or executor pages</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This website adheres to a strict anti-exploit policy. We do not host, link to, or publish Roblox scripts, auto-merge macros, or exploit executors. Third-party scripting tools compromise your account safety, trigger anti-cheat bans, and violate the Roblox Terms of Service.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Using unauthorized client modifications or automated macros ruins the fair play spirit of the game and exposes your device to malicious downloads. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> promotes building your base legitimately, ensuring that your achievements remain completely secure and cheat-free.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Play fair and build your nuclear tycoon base legitimately to ensure your progress remains secure.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">No fake rewards</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Unlike many spam sites that promise infinite free cash boosts, free admin gamepasses, or unlockable rebirths, we verify all promo codes before publishing. If an active reward is listed on this site, it has been confirmed in-game or sourced directly from verified developer patch notes.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Relying on false promises only leads to frustration. Our <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> filters out community noise to ensure you only spend time on working, active gift codes that successfully reward your tycoon with verified boosts and multipliers.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Unverified community claims are kept under pending status to filter out misleading clickbait rewards.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Rebirth mechanics</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Rebirthing is essential for late-game progression. Doing a rebirth resets your active cash and missile levels but grants permanent stats multipliers. These multipliers allow you to spawn higher base-tier missiles instantly, bypassing early-game merge lag and accelerating tycoon upgrades.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Knowing when to trigger a rebirth is the key to maintaining top speed. If your cash flow stalls and weapon upgrades feel too expensive, it is time to rebirth. Following our <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> strategy allows you to optimize your rebirth timing, ensuring you keep your tycoon efficiency at maximum capacity.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Always perform rebirths as soon as your upgrade targets slow down to optimize your overall progression speed.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section faq-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 32px; color: var(--color-yellow); font-family: var(--font-display);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; gap: 24px;">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. What should I upgrade first in Merge a Nuke?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. Beginners should prioritize upgrading <strong>Spawn Tier</strong> first. This allows the spawner to drop higher-tier missiles directly (such as Tier 2 or 3), which reduces the tedious number of manual merges required to reach S-Tier nukes.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. How do I get free nukes at the start?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. You can claim 5 free starting nukes by liking the game on Roblox, joining the official <strong>"Nuke The Game"</strong> developer group, and then clicking the in-game noticeboard at your base island.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. What is the benefit of a base Lock shield?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. The base lock shield protects your island from rival nuclear strikes. Activating the lock prevents other players from siphoning your currency or resetting your missile progress while you are actively merging or offline.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="guide" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
